Minjurochong  delegates and football team from South Korea welcomed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- A meeting of workers in Pyongyang was held at the Central Workers Hall today to welcome delegates of the South Korean Confederation of Trade Unions (Minjurochong) with chairman Ri Kap Yong as chief leader and with vice-chairman and chairman of reunification Ri Kyu Jae as leader and its workers' football team for reunification who have come to participate in the " soccer game of workers in the north and south for reunification."   
   Chairman Ryom Sun Gil of the central committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea in his welcoming speech extended warm militant solute to "Minjurochong"  delegates and the football team and  to all the workers of South Korea including "Minjurochong"  vigorously struggling under the slogan of independence, democracy and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The " soccer game of workers in the north and south for reunification,"    the first of its kind since the division of the country that lasted for over half a century, is a great auspicious event in opening an avenue of solidarity and unity between the workers in the north and south. this will be a great patriotic deed for showing a practical example of the working class, the symbol of unity, in reviving the national football game which was traditionally held in Pyongyang and Seoul alternately and achieving national reconciliation and great unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Since its founding "Minjurochong"  has undauntedly struggled for workers' vital rights, democracy and reunification of the country holding aloft the flag of independence, democracy and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   All the workers in the north will actively support their struggle in every way in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The game will mark an important occasion to bring a thaw in the long frozen ties between the workers in the north and the south and, furthermore, serve as a good basis of making a new turning point in the solidarity and unity among all patriotic pro-reunification movement organizations in the days ahead. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He hoped that the first good step taken for solidarity and unity between the workers in the north and the south through this soccer game would pave the broad way for independence, democracy and reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Chairman Ri Kap Yong of "Minjurochong"  in his reply speech said that the delegation of " Minjurochong"   extended with ardent desire for reunification hearty greetings to the northerners on behalf of 13 million workers and all other South Koreans aspiring after reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We have become fighters who will devote themselves to the reunification, always remembering the welcome accorded to us and the ardent feelings for reunification expressed on every occasion, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The workers in the south have never forgotten such words as hearty aspirations for reunification and compatriots, he said, and asked the workers in the north not to forget that they are always with their fellows who have such feelings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Wherever we went in Pyongyang, we have seen sincere hope, he noted, stressing: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We have come to Pyongyang at the risk of our lives in order to achieve the reunification of the country, turn this world into one for us workers and join hands with our comrades in the north.

Mansudae Windasia Joint-Venture Company
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- The Mansudae Windasia Joint-Venture Company is massproducing ornaments for women.
   Its products include finger-ring, necklace, brooch,  bracelet, ring and plastic button of scores of varieties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The company produces nearly 400,000 items every year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   These ornaments are made of rare metals (gold, silver and copper) and of various kinds of natural jewels such as ruby, sapphire and crystal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Its products are now in hot demand in Asian and European countries, including China, Japan, France and Italy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The company situated in the compound of the Mansudae Art Studio, a comprehensive fine art creative centre of Korea, was commissioned in April 1994. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The company has over 400 uptodate facilities of 40 odd kinds, including gilding, casting and grinding machines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The company has collaborated with the Windasia company of Japan since October 1997. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Mansudae Windasia Joint-Venture Company receives orders for more than 100,000 items each year.

KCNA on S. Korean warhawks' planned introduction of latest planes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- The South Korean warhawks are reportedly planning to purchase from the united states eight uptodate spy planes equipped with such electronic information-gathering devices as video recording and telecommunications over April 2000-2001.
   They are now asserting that they will be able to gather by themselves  information on the north for which they relied upon the united states so far through the planes capable of video recording areas as far as north of Sinuiju and observing areas up to south of Pyongyang and Wonsan from the sky 40 to 50 kilometers south of the Military Demarcation Line (MDL). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The planned purchase of the planes aimed at further intensifying the aerial espionage on the DPRK, is another grave military provocation to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As is already known, the aerial espionage on the DPRK has been mainly carried on by the united states and, not content with it, the South Korean rulers said they would take it upon themselves. this eloquently shows what a reckless phase their bellicose attempt to carry into practice the north-targeted war scenario has reached.
   Some days ago, the South Korean hawks announced they were going to purchase from the united states 100 "Popeye"  missiles capable of destroying "  missile"    bases of North Korea and even the long-range artillery in the area along the MDL, in the event of emergency. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The planned introduction of uptodate spy planes which synchronizes with the purchase of the "Popeye"  missiles for attack, can never be viewed as an accidental coincidence, as they are under way under a detailed and premeditated operational plan.
   It is a silly operational attempt for the South Korean hawks to seek to militarily suffocate the northern half of Korea by making a preemptive missile attack on military objects in the north, including the " missile bases"  on the basis of results of " minute espionage"  on them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Therefore, they should not act rashly, clearly mindful that their operational attempt is no more than a daydream and it will bring only destruction to them.

KCNA on Japanese diet's endorsement of bill on " Hinomaru" and " Kimigayo"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- The Japanese diet on August 9 endorsed a bill on approving the "Hinomaru"  to be a national flag and the " Kimigayo"  a national anthem. the endorsement of the bill sought by the Japanese authorities at last despite denunciation and rejection from the world public is an intolerable insult to the peoples of the countries which were subjected to aggression by Japan in the past, including Korea and other Asian countries, as well as a challenge to the history desirous of a peaceful new century free from war.
   As everyone knows, the "Hinomaru"    and " Kimigayo"   were the standard and song of the Japanese imperialists' aggression army that drenched Korea and other Asian countries with blood. So, they are symbols of disgraceful aggression and war which should have already been thrown into the dustbin of history along with the defeat of the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Nevertheless, the Japanese reactionaries have persistently carried on political and military moves to legalize the revival of militarism and the move for re-invasion, far from liquidating the past though over half a century has passed since Japan's defeat in the Second World War. the diet's endorsement of the bill on the " Hinomaru"    and "Kimigayo"   is part of the moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As it contravens the purpose of Japan's post-war " peace constitution"   , it is no more than superconstitutional coup following the adoption of the legislation on the "Japan-U.S. defense cooperation guidelines" . &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   What can not be overlooked is the fact that the Japanese reactionaries carried out the endorsement in a provocative manner on the eve of August 15, underscoring their denial of the historic defeat and a sort of psychology of retaliation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They thus openly infused the idea of ultranationalism and revanchism into the Japanese people and did not bother to declare that the time has come to materialize their design for reinvasion of Korea and other Asian nations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   But, Japan should stop the silly acts of challenging the history, clearly mindful that Korea today is not Korea yesterday and Asia today is not Asia yesterday.

Press conference on just released DPRK government statement
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- A press conference was held at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel today in connection with the just released statement of the DPRK government which accused Japan once again of its 100-year-long history of criminal policy toward Korea and clarified its principled stand toward the present state of DPRK-Japan relations on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of Korea's liberation. it was attended by Korean and foreign reporters.
   Speaking at the press conference, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Pak Tong Chun mentioned the motive of the publication of the statement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He noted: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Now that Japan is attempting to see the century out without properly repenting of the unprecedented crimes it committed against the Korean people and without dropping the hostile policy towards the DPRK it has pursued throughout the century, the DPRK government recalled Japan's history of crimes and clarified its principled stand toward it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As mentioned in the DPRK government statement, in a nutshell, the Korea policy pursued by Japan for a hundred years was aimed at exterminating, dividing, alienating, excluding and antagonising the Korean nation. that is why Japan cannot be termed  otherwise than the sworn enemy of the Korean people as it committed too many hideous crimes against them to expiate.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The improvement of bilateral relations means, in essence,  liquidating the crimes Japan committed against the Korean people and, on this basis, establishing new good-neighbourly relations in the interests of the peoples of the two countries and in conformity with the requirements of the times. but Japan is avoiding liquidation of the past with the century nearing its end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Though a generation is replaced by another and a new century arrives at the end of the old one, Japan can never flee from its legal and moral obligation to make a thorough apology and compensation to the Korean people for all its past crimes.
   He reclarified the principled stand of the DPRK government that Japan cannot see in the 21st century without any difficulty as long as the present serious state of the relations with the DPRK remains unsettled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Then he answered questions put by Korean and foreign reporters.
